Consider the semi-definite program:
\begin{align*}
\text{minimize}\quad & \mathbf{X}_{2,2}\\
\text{subject to}\quad & \mathbf{X} - \begin{bmatrix}
1 & 0\\
0 & -1
\end{bmatrix} \succeq 0\\
& \begin{bmatrix}
1 & 0\\
0 & 2
\end{bmatrix} - \mathbf{X} \succeq 0
\end{align*}

Find the optimal value and the optimal solution $\mathbf{X}$.
